                    Reviewed on 7/14/2015 10:10 AM

                    <div class="full_review_text">
                        <p>Pitch Perfect 2 + dinner at Tropisueno was aca-awesome! Chips & Guac + margaritas make me a happy girl, even though I'm slightly allergic to tequila ;) I came here w a coworker of mine aka my work boyfriend for dinner. We made reservations in advance for 530p. It was walking distance from work and close to the theatre. We walked in and the bar area was packed w those who were there for HH already. I loved the setup, furniture and decor of the place-- it makes it a fun and casual environment! We grabbed some house margaritas and headed to our table. (mMm, margaritas!) He ordered the carne asada plate and I ordered chicken enchiladas. The portions are big and I would recommend sharing! Although my coworker has a hole in his stomach and was able to finish his plate + half of mine. I would say this place kept their food somewhat authentic without Americanizing it too much-- I'll be back again when I crave for Mexican food, which will probably be next week! I also reached out recently to see if I could buy out the venue for a private work outing but turns out they only close the restaurant down for 1 day of the month and they were already booked for Sept, boo! Ah well, next time!</p>
                    </div>
                    <br/>
                    <div class="review_quicklinks">
                        <ul class="floatRight">
                            <li>
                                <a href="#">Useful</a>
                            </li>
